### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

router


### Description

Routing to a path with queryParams will route into something like: `xyz?param=value` which works as expected. But when you are on a page with that URL (some URL with query params) and reload the page, you will get an exception like:
`Error: Cannot match any routes. URL Segment: 'xyz%3Fparam%3Dvalue'`! in fact, the `?` and `=` marks are changed into  `%3F` and `%3D` and the router gets confused!

I thought this was related to my browser but the issue exists on both chrome and firefox! another check is that query params work fine on other websites e.x. GitHub. I can reload [this url](https://github.com/angular/angular/issues/new?assignees=&labels=&template=1-bug-report.yaml) with no issues! So it seems to be s.th. wrong with angular!

